Linear Discriminant Analysis (coded from scratch)¶

In [3]:
# Function for training/learning the LDA prediction rule
def lda_train(data):
    # Data is a n times (p+1) panda frame, with the last column corresponds to the target
    keys = data.keys() # get names of columns
    p = keys.size -1 # dimension of x
    class_names = data.species.unique()
    K = class_names.size # number of classes
    n = data.shape[0] # number of observations
    
    # Compute the MLE 
    datagroup = data.groupby(keys[-1]) # group the data by their class
    pi = datagroup[keys[-1]].count()/n # frequencies of each class       
    mu = datagroup.mean().T # mean for each class 
    sigma_perclass = datagroup.cov(ddof=0) # covariance matrix within each class
    # Common covariance matrix Sigma
    sigma = 0
    for k in range(K):
        sigma = sigma + pi[class_names[k]]*sigma_perclass.loc[class_names[k]]
    
    # Compute eigendecomposition of Sigma and transformed cluster means
    #U, D, U_tr = svd(sigma)
    D, U = eigh(sigma)
    U_tr= U.T
    D_sqrinv = np.diag(1/np.sqrt(D))
    
    mu_star = pd.DataFrame(data=np.empty([p,K]),columns = class_names)
    for idx in mu_star.keys(): # for each class
        mu_star[idx] = D_sqrinv @ U_tr @ mu[idx].values.reshape(p,1)
    return U_tr, D_sqrinv, mu_star, pi
    

U_tr, D_sqrinv, mu_star, pi = lda_train(iris2D)
    
# Learned prediction rule
def lda_predict(x, U_tr, D_sqrinv, mu_star, pi):
    x = x.T # convert x to a column vector
    x_star = D_sqrinv @ U_tr @ x  # Transform x
    dis = cdist(x_star.T, mu_star.T) # Compute the distance between the transformed x and cluster means
    yhat = np.argmin(-2*np.log(pi.values) + dis**2, axis = 1) # return the prediction
    yhat = pd.DataFrame(mu_star.keys()[yhat], columns = [pi.name]) # convert to a data frame    
    return yhat

x = pd.DataFrame([[2, 1], [4, 1]], index=['petal_length','petal_width'])
yhat = lda_predict(x, U_tr, D_sqrinv, mu_star, pi) 
print(yhat)

# Look at prediction over a range of values
x1 = np.arange(0, 7, 0.1)
x2 = np.arange(0, 2.5, 0.1)
xx1, xx2 = np.meshgrid(x1, x2)
xtest = np.column_stack([xx1.reshape(-1,1), xx2.reshape(-1,1)])
xtest = pd.DataFrame(xtest, columns=['petal_length','petal_width'])
ytest_lda = lda_predict(xtest, U_tr, D_sqrinv, mu_star, pi) 

iristest_lda = pd.concat([xtest, ytest_lda], axis = 1)
plt.figure()
sns.scatterplot(data=iristest_lda, x='petal_length', y='petal_width',
                                         hue = 'species', style= 'species', markers=["o", "s", "D"], legend = None)

LDA on Iris (with Scikit-learn)¶

In [4]:
# Using Scikit-learn
from sklearn.discriminant_analysis import LinearDiscriminantAnalysis
LDAclassifier = LinearDiscriminantAnalysis()
LDAclassifier.fit(X, y)

# Predict the values on the same grid as before
ytest_lda = LDAclassifier.predict(xtest)  # gives the same value as with the above function

# Plot the results (same as before)
iristest_lda = pd.concat([xtest, pd.DataFrame(ytest_lda, columns=['species'])], axis = 1)
plt.figure()
sns.scatterplot(data=iristest_lda, x='petal_length', y='petal_width',
                                         hue = 'species', style= 'species', markers=["o", "s", "D"], legend = None)
if svfigs:
    plt.savefig(svdir + 'iris2Dtest2.png', bbox_inches = 'tight')
